This paper is about dynamic topic modeling in natural language processing (NLP) research, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a novel unsupervised neural dynamic topic model, which involves deep learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and replicated softmax, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed model in terms of topic interpretation and evolution, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI).
